    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. The 6 not-assessed factors are consistent with ASME V&V 40 Table 1 scoping guidance for MRL 2 Class II devices. The relative hemolysis index QOI is directly linked to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1), and validation NRMSE of 8.3% is within acceptable bounds for this model risk level. The assessment team concludes the CFD model provides sufficient credibility to support identification of worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the CPB device.",
